subSubSection.paragraph:
Descriptive notes.
Head—body 94-114 mm, tail 59-61 mm, hindfoot 18-20 mm. No specific data are available for body weight. Similar to the Naked-tail Brush-furred Rat (
L. nudicaudus
) and the Western Brush-furred Rat (
L. sikapusi
), Hutterer’s Brushfurred Rat has dark brown, harshly unspeckled dorsum and red belly. Feet are short. Tail is short, 50-70% of head-body length. Rostrum is wide and high, and t3 cusp is absent on M*.
